parameter 1: Streaming versions available via Netflix have an alternate soundtrack (presumably for copyright reasons) replacing "It's In His Kiss" with a modern rap/hip hop song.
parameter 2: The original 1981 HBO broadcast version does not show the entire Williamstown Theater Festival play. Instead it opens with a scene of Dr. Watson narrating the details of what is not shown. He fills in backstory for what is only implied in the deleted portion. His narrative then fades into the remainder of the play's Act I. This version ends with the final curtain of the play.
parameter 3: The show runs for 60 minutes, and in the UK airs on channel BBC1 which shows programs without commercials. The show has been re-named MI-5 for American broadcasts on the A&E network, and each episode is edited down to approx 44 minutes to include commercials in a 60 minute time slot.
